message.content:
We start by extracting the key numbers from the ending balances (we use the ending or average values as needed):

1. Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio 
 • Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –1,028,375.55  
 • Total Current Liabilities = 378,850.51  
  Ratio = –1,028,375.55 / 378,850.51 ≈ –2.71

2. Debt to Equity Ratio 
 • Total Liabilities are taken as the difference between Total Liabilities and Owner’s Equity. Here the Balance Sheet shows:  
  Total Liabilities and Owner's Equity = 14,214,117.02  
  Total Owner's Equity = 13,835,266.51  
  Thus, Total Liabilities = 14,214,117.02 – 13,835,266.51 = 378,850.51  
  Ratio = 378,850.51 / 13,835,266.51 ≈ 0.0274 (or about 0.03)

3. Total Asset Turnover Ratio  
 • Total Revenue (from the income statement) = 2,637,011.03  
 • Total Assets at beginning = 13,000,000.00 and ending = 14,214,117.02  
  Average Total Assets = (13,000,000.00 + 14,214,117.02) / 2 = 13,607,058.51  
  Ratio = 2,637,011.03 / 13,607,058.51 ≈ 0.19

4. Quick Ratio  
 • Quick Assets are defined as current assets excluding inventory.  
  Ending Current Assets = 9,221,098.50  
  Inventory = 203,000.00  
  Quick Assets = 9,221,098.50 – 203,000.00 = 9,018,098.50  
 • Total Current Liabilities = 378,850.51  
  Quick Ratio = 9,018,098.50 / 378,850.51 ≈ 23.79

5. Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
 This is essentially the same as (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities) so the value is –2.71

6. Return on Equity (ROE)  
 • Net Profit = 835,266.51  
 • Owner's Equity at beginning = 13,000,000.00, at ending = 13,835,266.51  
  Average Owner’s Equity = (13,000,000.00 + 13,835,266.51) / 2 = 13,417,633.255  
  ROE = 835,266.51 / 13,417,633.255 ≈ 0.0623, or about 6.23%

7. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
 • Accounts Receivable (beginning = 0, ending = 2,117,339.65)  
  Average Accounts Receivable = (0 + 2,117,339.65) / 2 = 1,058,669.825  
 • Total Revenue = 2,637,011.03  
  Ratio = 2,637,011.03 / 1,058,669.825 ≈ 2.49

Thus, the results can be summarized as follows:

{
  "solution": {
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-2.71",
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.03",
    "Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.19",
    "Quick Ratio": "23.79",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-2.71",
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "6.23%",
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "2.49"
  }
}
